{
  "text": "In our proofs we require one further condition on the a-priori measure \u00b5 0 , which guarantees that exponential decay of connected spin-spin correlation functions holds at large values of |Re h|, assuming only that |Im h| \u2264 const. \u00d7 |Re h|. This will be proven with the help of a \"large-field cluster expansion\"; see Section 3. Large-field cluster expansions have been developed in [CITATION_1] in the context of two-dimensional continuum euclidian field theories. For reasons that will become apparent below, it is useful to parametrize the constant in the above inequality as const. = tan \u03b1, for \u03b1 contained in (0, ). Namely, we assume that,",
